After two seasons with the club, Kone moved to Serie A club Brescia.

people.name: Panagiotis Kone
people.aboutText: John Alan White (born 26 July 1986) is an English professional footballer who plays as a defender for Southend United.

people.name: Alec Martinez
people.aboutText: Miriam Katherine McDonald (born July 26, 1987) is a former Canadian actress.

people.name: Miriam McDonald
people.aboutText: Alec Martinez (born July 26, 1987) is an American professional ice hockey player currently playing for the Los Angeles Kings of the National Hockey League (NHL).

people.name: Fredy Montero
people.aboutText:
Fredy Henkyer Montero Muñoz (born 26 July 1987), known as Fredy Montero, is a Colombian professional footballer who plays as a forward for Portuguese club Sporting Clube de Portugal.
Montero is Seattle's all-time top scorer in official club competitions, having scored 60 goals since joining the club in 2009. Montero has been called up to the Colombian national team 5 times, scoring once in an unofficial match against Catalonia.

people.name: Sayaka Akimoto
people.aboutText: Sayaka Akimoto (秋元 才加, Akimoto Sayaka, born July 26, 1988 in Matsudo, Chiba), is a Japanese idol singer, dancer, actress, television host, and model. She is best known as being a member of the Japanese idol girl group AKB48, where she had served as the captain of Team K and has also been involved in the AKB48 sub-unit Diva.

people.name: Francia Raisa
people.aboutText:
Areti Ketime (Greek: Αρετή Κετιμέ) (Athens July 26, 1989) is a singer and santoor player from Greece. She sings traditional Greek songs of various music genres.
Ketime was born and raised in Athens, but her origins come from the greater area of Mesolongi.

people.name: Areti Ketime
people.aboutText: Francia Raisa Almendárez (born July 26, 1988) is an American actress. She is sometimes credited as Francia Almendárez. Raisa is most notable for her roles in Bring It On: All or Nothing, where she plays a tough Latina cheerleader named Leti and in The Secret Life of the American Teenager as Adrian Lee.

people.name: Ivian Sarcos
people.aboutText:
Janelle Ann Caren Quintana Manahan (born 26 July 1989) is an actress in the Philippines. She started showbusiness when she joined ABS-CBN's reality talent search Star Circle National Teen Quest as Janelle Manahan and made it to the top 6.
After her supporting stint in SCQ Reload: OK Ako!

people.name: Janelle Quintana
people.aboutText:
Ivian Sarcos (born July 26, 1989 in Guanare, Venezuela) is a Venezuelan model and beauty queen who won Miss World 2011 on November 6, 2011 in London, United Kingdom. Sarcos is the sixth woman from Venezuela to win Miss World.
^ "Miss World Official Site: MISS WORLD 2011 is VENEZUELA".

people.name: Tyson Barrie
people.aboutText: Tyson Barrie (born July 26, 1991) is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenceman currently playing for the Colorado Avalanche of the National Hockey League (NHL). Barrie previously played for and captained the Kelowna Rockets of the Western Hockey League (WHL).

people.name: Marika Koroibete
people.aboutText: Marika Koroibete (born 26 July 1992) is a Fijian professional rugby league footballer who currently plays for the Melbourne Storm in the National Rugby League. He plays at wing and previously played for the Wests Tigers.

people.name: Elizabeth Gillies
people.aboutText: Taylor Michel Momsen (born July 26, 1993) is an American actress, musician and model. She is known for portraying the character of Jenny Humphrey on the CW television series Gossip Girl (2007–12) and Cindy Lou Who in Dr. Seuss' How the Grinch Stole Christmas (2000).

people.name: Taylor Momsen
people.aboutText: Elizabeth Egan "Liz" Gillies (born July 26, 1993) is an American actress and singer-songwriter, known for playing the role of Jade West on Victorious. She made her Broadway debut at age 15 in the musical 13, playing the character of Lucy.

people.name: Ella Leivo
people.aboutText: Holly Bodimeade (born 26 July 1995) is an English actress.

people.name: Holly Bodimeade
people.aboutText:
Ella Leivo (born 26 July 1994 in Tampere) is a Finnish tennis player.
On 28 July 2014, Leivo reached her best singles ranking of world number 1044. On 11 November 2013, she peaked at world number 788 in the doubles rankings.

people.name: Olivia Breen
people.aboutText: Olivia "Livvy" Breen (born 26 July 1996) is a Welsh Paralympian athlete, who competes mainly in T38 sprint events. In 2012 she qualified for the 2012 Summer Paralympics, selected for the T38 100m and 200m sprint and is also part of the T35-38 women's relay team. In 2014 she represented Wales at the Commonwealth Games.

people.name: Tatjana Vorobjova
people.aboutText:
Tatjana Vorobjova (Russian: Татьяна Воробьёва; born 26 July 1996 in Tallinn) is an Estonian tennis player.
Playing for Estonia at the Fed Cup, Vorobjova has a win–loss record of 4–7.

people.name: Maya Sakura
people.aboutText: Maya Sakura (さくら　まや, Sakura Maya, born Maya Kusano (草野真耶) on 26 July 1998 in Obihiro, Hokkaidō, Japan) is an enka singer and child actress. In 2008, she made her debut with the single "Tairyō Matsuri" (大漁まつり) at the age of 10. In 2009, she received a "New Artist" award at the 51st Annual Japan Record Awards, becoming the youngest person to do so.
